name: FontAwesome

unions.name: Animation
unions.comment: Font Awesome's built-in animations. iconWithOptions print Solid [ Animation Pulse ] [] --

unions.name: HtmlTag
unions.comment: Surrounding tag for icon and logo elements. Defaults to `` if not set. iconWithOptions truck Regular [ HtmlTag Span ] [] --

unions.name: Option
unions.comment: Font Awesome specific options. Any number of these can be passed in when generating an icon or logo. If any option is repeated, then only one will be selected. However, there is no guarantee as to which option will be selected, so please only use each option once per icon or logo. Including the `HasBorder` option will draw a border around the icon or logo. iconWithOptions quoteLeft Solid [ HasBorder ] [] -- Including the `HasFixedWidth` option will set a fixed width on the icon or logo. All elements with this option will have the same width. iconWithOptions diamond Regular [ HasFixedWidth ] [] -- Including the `InvertColor` option will invert the color of the icon or logo. iconWithOptions home Light [ InvertColor ] [] -- The `Mask` option allows you to set an outer icon or logo which sits behind the main Font Awesome element. It only works if you are using SVG elements. iconWithOptions pencil Regular [ Mask comment Solid ] [] -- Documentation for the other options appears with their type definitions below.

unions.name: Pull
unions.comment: Options for pulling a logo or icon to the left or right. iconWithOptions fileImage Light [ Pull Left ] [] --

unions.name: Size
unions.comment: Font Awesome's alternative size options. Valid values for the `Mult` options are integers 2 - 10 inclusive. iconWithOptions cog Solid [ Size ExtraSmall ] [] -- iconWithOptions list Regular [ Size (Mult 4) ] [] --

unions.name: Style
unions.comment:
Every icon has one variation per style. Some of the Solid, most of the
`Regular`, and all of the `Light` variations require Font Awesome Pro, so if
you are using the free version then please refer to Font Awesome's icon library
to determine which styles are available to you.

Note that brand logos are only available in a single style, and so they will
ignore whatever style is given.

unions.name: Transform
unions.comment: The `Transform` option accepts transformation instructions for the element. See Font Awesome's documentation for supported instructions. iconWithOptions bicycle light [ Transform [ Shrink 3, ShiftUp 6, Rotate 45 ] ] [] --

values.name: icon
values.comment: Create an icon with the default style (`Solid` for icons), default tag (``), and no additional options or attributes. icon file -- icon pinterest --

values.name: iconWithOptions
values.comment: Create an icon with the given options and attributes. iconWithOptions spinner Solid [ Animation Spin ] [] -- iconWithOptions question Light [ HasBorder, Pull Right ] [ Html.Attributes.title "Question"] -- iconWithOptions info Regular [ HasFixedWidth, Size Large, HtmlTag Span ] [] -- iconWithOptions snapchat Solid [ Transform [ Grow 5 ] ] --
values.type: FontAwesome.Icon -> FontAwesome.Style -> List.List FontAwesome.Option -> List.List (Html.Attribute msg) -> Html.Html msg

values.name: useCss
values.comment:
A convenience helper for including Font Awesome CSS on your page using their CDN.
Place this inside your `<head>` tag.

Note that some features will not work if you choose CSS rather than SVGs.
Please refer to Font Awesome's documentation for details.

name: FontAwesome.Layers
comment:
This module enables the layers feature of Font Awesome 5. Layers allows you
to stack any number of Font Awesome icons and elements, as well as overlay text
or counter badges.

Note that this feature requires using SVG Font Awesome elements.


# Entry point

@docs layers


# Options and layers

@docs IconLayer, LayerOption, BadgePosition

unions.name: IconLayer
unions.comment: A layer consisting of any Font Awesome icon or logo.

unions.name: LayerOption
unions.comment:
Other options for a set of layers.

Including the `LayerHasFixedWidth` option will align all layers.

Including the `TextLayer` option will place the given text on top
of your layers element.

Including the `Badge` option adds a badge with the given text on top
of your element. This is often used to display a counter.

values.name: layers
values.comment: Create a layered Font Awesome element. layers [ IconLayer envelope Solid [] [] ] [ LayerHasFixedWidth , Badge "821" TopLeft [] ] -- -- -- 821 --
values.type: List.List (FontAwesome.Layers.IconLayer msg) -> List.List (FontAwesome.Layers.LayerOption msg) -> Html.Html msg
